          <td width="414" valign="top"><p><img src="images/t_welcome.gif" width="187" height="19"><br>  
              Welcome to AustNet, a safe IRC network with servers in all corners   
              of the globe. To learn more about how to start chatting on the AustNet   
              Internet Relay Chat Network, read our <a href="support/newuser.html">New   
              User's Guide</a>. While you're here, why not explore <a href="support/services/index.html">services</a>   
              which AustNet makes available to you for free?</p>  
            <p>AustNet emphasises your safety while you are on our network. Unlike   
              other IRC networks, we have introduced Virtual World, which masks   
              your real address and prevents attacks - keeping you safe. You can   
              find out more information about Virtual World on the <a href="virtualworld/index.html">information   
              page</a>.</p>  
            <p><img src="images/t_news.gif" width="187" height="19">
            	
<p><a href="/community/news-admin.php"><img src="/images/news-admin.gif" height="50" width="50" align="left" border=0></a><strong>New testlinked server - swiftdsl</strong><br>AustNet has testlinked a new Australian server - swiftdsl.nsw.au.austnet.org. The new server will help AustNet cope with the increasing number of Australian clients. During the testlink, you can connect to the server using /server irc.swiftdsl.com.au. Welcome to the server and to its admin Testius! <br><div class=newscredits>August 1st 9:46am, Submitted by <a href="mailto:stevie@kas.net.au">Stevie</a></div>
<p><a href="/community/news-general.php"><img src="/images/news-interest.gif" height="50" width="50" align="left" border=0></a><strong>xchat 2.0.4</strong><br>The latest version of the open source XChat IRC client was released today. The change log can be found <a href="http://www.xchat.org/changelog.txt" target="_blank">Here</a> and can be downloaded from the <a href="http://www.xchat.org/download.html">xchat download</a> page. Windows binaries are not yet available. <br><div class=newscredits>July 31st 7:17pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:karl@austnet.org">Karl</a></div>
<p><a href="/community/news-general.php"><img src="/images/news-interest.gif" height="50" width="50" align="left" border=0></a><strong>Project-Dolphin.nl team passes 30million</strong><br>The AustNet project dolphin team has passed the 30 million keys mark and is currently ranked 37th. <a href=http://www.project-dolphin.nl/team.php?tid=390 target=_blank>Click Here</a> to see the break down.<br />
<br />
For those of you that aren't aware of what project-dolphin.nl is, its a key stroke counting "project" that sprung up after the death of the original projectdolphin.com.&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="/community/news-general.php">More</a><br><div class=newscredits>July 4th 5:33pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:karl@austnet.org">Karl</a></div>
<p><a href="/community/news-general.php"><img src="/images/news-interest.gif" height="50" width="50" align="left" border=0></a><strong>XChat 2.0.3 is out!</strong><br>XChat have released version 2.0.3 of their popular IRC client. The new build includes several bug fixes and also addresses current stability issues.&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="/community/news-general.php">More</a><br><div class=newscredits>July 3rd 10:01am, Submitted by <a href="mailto:blase@austnet.org">Blase</a></div>
<p><a href="/community/news-general.php"><img src="/images/news-interest.gif" height="50" width="50" align="left" border=0></a><strong>Updated servers.ini for mIRC</strong><br>A fresh new list of IRC servers for mIRC is available for download. Servers.ini can be downloaded at http://www.mirc.co.uk/servers.ini&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="/community/news-general.php">More</a><br><div class=newscredits>June 27th 8:27pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:Blase@austnet.org">Blasé</a></div>
<p><a href="/community/news-network.php"><img src="/images/news-network.gif" height="50" width="50" align="left" border=0></a><strong>Spin.* adds new staff member</strong><br>One of our Australian client servers has added its first additional staff member since linking to the network nearly a year ago. We would like to congratulate and welcome robbie as a local operator on the server. <br><div class=newscredits>June 27th 3:20pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:cam@austnet.org">cam</a></div>
<p><a href="/community/news-admin.php"><img src="/images/news-admin.gif" height="50" width="50" align="left" border=0></a><strong>New ASD helpers</strong><br>Three new helpers have joined the ASD ranks. Seaner and RooK have been added at level 10, and saturn at level 51 (because he was a netpriest). Well done to these people! <br><div class=newscredits>June 21st 10:39am, Submitted by <a href="mailto:ed@austnet.org">ed</a></div>
<p><a href="/community/news-general.php"><img src="/images/news-interest.gif" height="50" width="50" align="left" border=0></a><strong>Austnet Design Competition Winner Announced</strong><br>A winner for the first AustNet Design Competition has been announced. Nizmo narrowly beat some great competition entries, to win a wonderful web hosting package donated by Maxmax6 Professional Hosting - including one years free hosting and a year's registration of a .net, .com or .org domain. Thank you to all those people who entered the competition and watch <A HREF="http://community.austnet.org">http://community.austnet.org</A> for other coming competitions! <br><div class=newscredits>June 16th 5:31pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:hippychick@austnet.org">Hippychick</a></div>
<p><a href="/community/news-alerts.php"><img src="/images/news-warning.gif" height="50" width="50" align="left" border=0></a><strong>eggdrop 1.6.15 op status bug</strong><br>Eggdrop 1.6.15 will incorrectly report that some non-opped users in a channel are opped. This may pose a serious problem, depending on what tcl files are used. The bug does not exist in versions 1.6.13 and earlier. It is recommended that users of 1.6.15 revert to an earlier version. <br><div class=newscredits>June 15th 6:10pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:dathi@appello.net">Deoau</a></div>
<p><a href="/community/news-general.php"><img src="/images/news-interest.gif" height="50" width="50" align="left" border=0></a><strong>Austnet competition entries</strong><br>Entries have now closed for the first AustNet Design competition, where AustNet users were invited to design a button that could be used to link to the Austnet website. The top 10 buttons are now <A HREF="http://community.austnet.org/competitions/compentries.html">on display</a> in the Community section of the site, and the winner of a web hosting and domain package from Maxmax6 Professional Web Hosting will be announced on Sunday 15th June, 2003. <br><div class=newscredits>June 11th 8:03am, Submitted by <a href="mailto:hippychick@austnet.org">Hippychick</a></div>
 
